title: Economic Expansion
subtitle: The economy is growing steadily.
new-page: true
view-if: economic_expansion >= 85 and unemployed <= 6 and inflation <= 6 and not spd_in_government
on-arrival: economic_expansion = 0; capital_strike_progress -= 4 if capital_strike_progress >= 4; capital_strike_progress = 0 if capital_strike_progress < 4; budget += 1; workers_spd -= 5*bourgeois_power; workers_spd -= 5*(1-(socialism/100)); new_middle_spd -= 5*bourgeois_power; new_middle_spd -= 5*(1-(socialism/100)); old_middle_spd -= 8; rural_spd -= 5*bourgeois_power; rural_spd -= 5*(1-(socialism/100)); new_middle_ddp += 5 if not in_right_coalition; old_middle_dvp += 4; new_middle_dvp += 3; workers_z += 2; workers_ddp += 2 if not in_right_coalition; workers_dnvp += 2 if in_right_coalition; old_middle_dnvp += 5 if in_right_coalition; rural_dvp += 3; rural_dvp += 3 if not in_right_coalition; rural_dnvp += 3 if in_right_coalition; inflation += 0.4; socialism -= socialism -= economic_growth*bourgeois_power; bourgeois_power += (economic_growth/100) if bourgeois_power < 1
tags: event

= Economic Expansion

The German economy has been growing steadily for an extended period of time, and has low inflation and unemployment. The government is rewarded by additional tax revenue from the same tax rates, and popularity. We are left out by these developments.